We are trying to use the plugin but it seems like the plugin is not able to prime/purge the cache for domains that are being mapped. The plugin will create the initial page cache properly but then the cache doesn't seem to update.</p>
<p>We found that the plugin works correctly for sites without a mapped domain (multisite.com/muclient) but when it is using a mapped domain, it will not purge the cache found in the muclient.com folder (where it created the initial cache). We thought that maybe it was a permission issue but the cache folders where it is not linked to a mapped domain seem to work just fine.</p>
<p>Where do you think the issue is? Is it an issue in the root .htaccess? </p>
<p>Thank you for reading this.</p>
